cs.CG, cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.GR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new method for visualizing implicit curves in 2D and 3D space based on numerical continuation and critical point methods. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is also likely as the paper deals with real algebraic curves and their singularities. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the algorithm is based on numerical continuation and critical point methods. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the paper is about visualizing curves. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions applications such as solving bi-parametric polynomial systems.
